        "pattern": "CQRS-Lite (Separate Read Cache from Write Path)",
        "rationale": "The in-memory courier cache serves reads (candidate filtering) while the DB serves writes (assignment). This is not full CQRS — no separate read store or event sourcing. Just enough separation to keep the hot path fast without compromising consistency."
