      "gains": "Reduces DB transaction scope from scanning thousands of couriers to locking one of ~10 pre-filtered candidates. Keeps DB transaction under 50ms.",
      "sacrifices": "Cache can be stale by ~100-500ms. A courier who just became unavailable might still appear in candidates — but the DB transaction (SELECT FOR UPDATE) catches this safely. Stale cache costs one wasted DB lock attempt, not correctness.",
